    <summary>Advanced automation and system management tool for Windows</summary>
    <description>
Redball is an advanced automation and system management tool designed for Windows environments. It provides powerful input injection capabilities, system monitoring, and enterprise-grade security features.

## Features

- **Input Injection Engine**: Automated testing with precise input control
- **System Monitoring**: Real-time analytics and performance tracking
- **Enterprise Security**: Audit logging and compliance features
- **RESTful API**: Easy integration with existing workflows
- **Delta Updates**: Efficient update system with differential patching
- **Multi-Channel Releases**: Support for stable, beta, and dev channels

## Installation

This package requires .NET 10 Desktop Runtime.

After installation:
1. Launch Redball from the Start Menu
2. Configure your automation workflows
3. Access the web dashboard at http://localhost:3500

## Documentation

Full documentation available at: https://github.com/ArMaTeC/Redball/wiki

## Package Specifics

- Uses the official NSIS installer
- Installs for all users (machine-wide)
- Creates Start Menu shortcuts
- Registers file associations (.rdb files)
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/ArMaTeC/Redball/releases</releaseNotes>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="dotnet-desktopruntime-10" version="10.0.0" />
    </dependencies>
